<subSubSection id="C3443AECAF785D51FF4CAD7A75B6D9A7" pageId="6" pageNumber="113" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BE16967AF785D51FF4CAD7A75B6D9A7" blockId="6.[136,1059,825,912]" pageId="6" pageNumber="113">
COMMENTS: The male abdominal sternite VIII with a pair of projecting tips of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E12E4AF785D51FF10AD1A7756D947" authorityName="Bierig" authorityYear="1940" box="[136,314,857,880]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Megarthrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavosignatus">
<emphasis id="B92AB575AF785D51FF10AD1A7756D947" box="[136,314,857,880]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="113">M. flavosignatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is particularly notable. This feature is shared only with 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E12E4AF785D51FC17AD1A7277D947" authorityName="Sharp. These" authorityYear="1887" box="[911,1051,857,880]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Megarthrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zunilensis">
<emphasis id="B92AB575AF785D51FC17AD1A7277D947" box="[911,1051,857,880]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="113">M. zunilensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which has different male sexual characters. See comments under 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E12E4AF785D51FCDEAD3A75BFD9A7" authorityName="Sharp. These" authorityYear="1887" box="[838,979,889,912]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Megarthrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zunilensis">
<emphasis id="B92AB575AF785D51FCDEAD3A75BFD9A7" box="[838,979,889,912]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="113">M. zunilensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
